SABC employees at Auckland Park. JOHANNESBURG - SABC employees in Auckland Park are addressing their management in a heated meeting.
The public broadcaster's COO, Ian Plaatjies and Group Executive: News & Current Affairs, Phathiswa Magopeni are listening to angry employees. They are telling management they won't accept the latest round of restructuring. READ: Retrenchments to go ahead at SABC Employees are calling for the resignation of management. The SABC is planning to cut hundreds of jobs in the coming months. The broadcaster has recorded a loss of over R500-million in the 2019/2020 financial year.